What is a Table d’Hote?
A Table d’Hote is essentially a daily menu. Most restaurants post a Table d’Hote to let customers know what the chef feels is the best value he can offer that day. A Table d’Hote usually includes an appetizer, soup or salad course, a main course (usually a choice) sometimes dessert, and finally coffee or tea all for a fixed price. Sometimes the choices are items NOT featured on the restaurant’s regular menu. Table d’Hotes serve two main functions, to reward faithful clients of the restaurant and, because they are usually posted where the public can see them, to induce new clients to try the establishment through bargain prices. 
for more info visit http://www.tabledhote.com .